[ Laughing ]
They've done it again.

01:36.496 --> 01:39.624
<i>''Gigabytes.'' Wait-This isn't Weird.</i>

01:39.732 --> 01:42.257
<i>Why, there's no magazine
called Weird, is there?</i>

01:42.368 --> 01:45.929
<i>This is Wired.
It's about computers and technology.</i>

01:47.974 --> 01:51.466
Hey, look. There's a cybercafe
opening right here in Springfield.

01:51.578 --> 01:53.478
Will you take me, Dad? Please?

01:53.580 --> 01:55.571
I'll show you how to order pizza
over the Internet.

01:55.682 --> 01:58.048
The Internet? Is that thing still around?

01:58.151 --> 02:00.142
I know a Web site
that shows monkeys doin' it.

02:00.253 --> 02:02.483
Bart, the Internet is more
than a global pornography network.

02:02.589 --> 02:03.988
<i>- It's a-
- [ Horn Honks ]</i>

02:04.090 --> 02:07.856
- Come on, Lisa. Monkeys.
- [ Groans ]

02:11.931 --> 02:15.128
Ach. Let's see what's been captured
on the up-kilt camera.

02:15.235 --> 02:18.136
[ Beeps, Whirs ]

02:18.238 --> 02:21.298
Ew. This lass needs
a bit of grounds keeping.

02:21.407 --> 02:23.773
Eh? Aah! That's Willie!

02:24.878 --> 02:26.778
My name is Mary.

02:26.880 --> 02:29.644
I'm 45, heavy and willing
to settle for less.

02:30.984 --> 02:33.680
Wow. This Mary's got
the whole package.

02:34.787 --> 02:36.914
Wow, Dad. You're surfin' like a pro.

02:37.023 --> 02:40.424
Oh, yeah. I'm betting on jai alai
in the Cayman Islands.

02:40.527 --> 02:43.052
I invested in something
called News Corp-

02:43.163 --> 02:45.131
- Dad! That's Fox!
- [ Screams ]

02:45.231 --> 02:47.131
Undo! Undo!
[ Groans ]

02:47.233 --> 02:49.133
Dad, do we have any money left?

02:49.235 --> 02:51.863
Well, let's check
the old bank account.

02:51.971 --> 02:54.804
<i>- [ Beeps ]
- See? Even after my cyber squandering...</i>

02:54.908 --> 02:56.876
we've still got $1 ,200.

02:56.976 --> 03:00.173
- All right, dorks, this is a holdup.
- [ Gasping, Murmuring ]

03:00.280 --> 03:02.077
Oh, yes!

03:02.182 --> 03:04.377
Download to papa.

03:04.484 --> 03:09.615
- [ Beeping ]
- Yoink dot adios, back-slash losers.

03:10.924 --> 03:13.358
<i>- [ Groans ]
- [ Marge ] We were robbed?</i>

03:13.459 --> 03:17.896
You seem to know an awful lot
about this for an innocent person.

03:17.997 --> 03:20.727
We were saving that money
for our family vacation.

03:20.833 --> 03:23.563
Now we're gonna have
to start all over again.

03:23.670 --> 03:26.503
- [ Groans ]
- Aw, don't worry, sweetheart.

03:26.606 --> 03:30.633
I'll get us the money-
even if I have to get a second job.

03:39.385 --> 03:41.649
Evenin', neighbor.
Low on funds again?

03:41.754 --> 03:44.723
- Yes, sir.
- Now, Homer, we can't have you burglarizing us...

03:44.824 --> 03:47.122
every time you got a bill to pay.

03:47.227 --> 03:49.491
I know, sir. I'm sorry, sir.

03:51.130 --> 03:54.099
It's just that you and Maude live
like royalty in your fancy castle...

03:54.200 --> 03:58.000
while I got Marge trapped
over there like a pig in a mud beehive.

03:58.104 --> 04:00.595
Oh, we're-We're not
as well off as you think.

04:00.707 --> 04:03.335
We give to eight different churches
just to hedge our bets...

04:03.443 --> 04:05.707
and the Leftorium's business
has gone way down hill...

04:05.812 --> 04:08.212
since Leftopolis moved in next door.

04:08.314 --> 04:11.249
If you're not rich, then how come
you have a new refrigerator...

04:11.351 --> 04:13.512
an electric can opener,
a milk shake machine?

04:13.620 --> 04:15.554
[ Chuckling ]
We picked those up cheap.

04:15.655 --> 04:18.055
- They were evidence at a murder trial.
- Sweet.

04:18.156 --> 04:21.183
We got that tip at the Chuck Garabedian
Mega-Savings Seminar.

04:21.293 --> 04:23.353
- Go on.
- He taught us how to live...

04:23.463 --> 04:25.863
a Burt Reynolds lifestyle
on a Mac Davis income.

04:25.965 --> 04:28.195
We've already got tickets
for his next seminar.

04:28.301 --> 04:31.566
I think you'll find living thrifty
a lot more satisfying than stealing.

04:31.671 --> 04:34.003
Maybe you're right, Ned.

04:34.107 --> 04:36.632
Maybe you're right.

04:44.450 --> 04:47.248
Are you tired of missing out
on the good things in life-

04:47.353 --> 04:51.289
Family vacations,jet packs,
Solid Gold Dancers?

04:51.391 --> 04:53.416
There's only three left in the world.

04:53.526 --> 04:55.585
Well, stick around,
'cause I'm gonna tell you...

04:55.695 --> 04:59.392
<i>the 1 2 savings secrets
Wall Street won't tell you.</i>

04:59.499 --> 05:02.798
Then I'll show you the three ways
to get back to the highway-

05:02.902 --> 05:07.339
including one shortcut those
Wall Street fat cats don't want you to know.

05:07.440 --> 05:11.843
- [ Cheering ]
- Oh, here we go with the fat-cat bashing.

05:11.944 --> 05:15.880
Well, what do you expect?
These yokels are pure Baltic Avenue.

05:15.982 --> 05:19.145
[ Chuckles ]
Uh-oh! I'm late for the Short Line Railroad.

05:19.252 --> 05:22.050
[ Tires Squeal ]

05:22.155 --> 05:24.385
Let's start with mega secret number one:

05:24.490 --> 05:27.357
''Ya gotta squeeze every penny.''

05:27.460 --> 05:30.861
You see this tux? I got it cheap
'cause Roy Cohn died in it.

05:30.963 --> 05:32.931
- [ Murmuring ]
- That fancy yacht?

05:33.032 --> 05:35.660
A bargain, 'cause it smells like cat pee.

05:35.768 --> 05:39.226
<i>- [ Murmuring ]
- And those beautiful women?</i>

05:39.339 --> 05:41.432
- They used to be men.
- [ Groaning ]

05:41.541 --> 05:46.205
The point is, ya gotta squeeze every penny.
Come on, let me hear you.

05:46.312 --> 05:49.907
[ Together]
Squeeze every penny. Squeeze every penny.

05:50.016 --> 05:53.247
I'm squeezing. I'm squeezing it.

05:53.353 --> 05:56.652
- [ Slurping Sound ]
- Hey, I squeezed so hard it went into my hand.

05:56.756 --> 05:58.815
Oh, Homer, not again.

06:05.565 --> 06:06.827
Ew. We're gonna do our grocery
shopping at a 99-cent store?

06:06.933 --> 06:08.833
Well, maybe for your wedding.

06:10.203 --> 06:12.535
- [ Bart ] How about here?
- Not if we want that vacation.

06:19.812 --> 06:21.712
Look, Mom. They have your dress.

06:21.814 --> 06:25.614
[ Groans ]
Thirty-three cents? I paid almost double that.

06:27.453 --> 06:29.353
Blue?

06:29.455 --> 06:32.049
Wow! This plankton's only 33 cents.

06:32.158 --> 06:35.559
According to the Mexican
Council of Food...

06:35.661 --> 06:37.629
this expired two years ago.

06:37.730 --> 06:40.893
Sure, by their standards,
but we live in America.

06:41.000 --> 06:43.628
[ Chomping, Groaning ]

06:43.736 --> 06:47.035
This also says it can cause
red tide poisoning.

06:47.140 --> 06:49.438
But it's so cheap.

06:50.777 --> 06:53.871
<i>Well, let's see what's
in the old vacation fund.</i>

06:55.648 --> 06:57.775
Homer, you could have
just unscrewed the bottom.

06:57.884 --> 07:00.011
A little late for
''could-haves,'' Marge.

07:00.119 --> 07:02.644
I don't think there's
enough here for a vacation.

07:02.755 --> 07:05.656
There is for a Mega-Savings vacation.

07:05.758 --> 07:08.522
Chuck Garabedian says
you can fly mega cheap...

07:08.628 --> 07:10.619
if you don't care where you go.

07:10.730 --> 07:13.961
That's right.Just go to the airport
and wait for some no-shows.

07:14.066 --> 07:16.694
Then you can buy their seats
for a fraction of the price.

07:16.803 --> 07:18.771
Are you going through our garbage?

07:18.871 --> 07:21.863
That's right. You fat cats
didn't finish your plankton.

07:21.974 --> 07:23.908
Now it's mine.

07:27.447 --> 07:30.109
Hawaii, here we come.

07:30.216 --> 07:32.776
No. No. We're going to Paris. I can feel it.

07:32.885 --> 07:34.876
Come on, Transylvania.

07:34.987 --> 07:37.148
[ With Jamaican Accent ]
No, mon, let's go home toJamaica.

07:37.256 --> 07:39.952
I and I been in Babylon too long.

07:40.059 --> 07:43.893
<i>[ Woman On P.A.] Attention.
Flight 605 to Tokyo is ready for departure...</i>

07:43.996 --> 07:46.362
<i>and has four available
mega-saver seats.</i>

07:46.466 --> 07:48.934
- [ Both ] Yeah!
- Come on, Homer.Japan.

07:49.035 --> 07:53.904
No, notJapan,Jamaica. I wanna
pass the dutchie on the left-hand side.

07:54.006 --> 07:58.636
Never mind. Looks like the Flanders
are gonna get those seats anyway.

07:58.744 --> 08:01.941
Oh, so Flanders thinks
he can steal our vacation, huh?

08:02.982 --> 08:04.882
- [ Groans ]
- Come on!

08:06.552 --> 08:09.453
- Whoo!
- [ Horn Honking ]

08:09.555 --> 08:12.422
<i>- Sayonara, suckers.
- [ Snarls ]</i>

08:12.525 --> 08:15.824
Yea! The Simpsons
are going toJapan.

08:15.928 --> 08:17.828
<i>[ Gong Sounds ]</i>

08:17.930 --> 08:19.830
Hey, watch the gong,jerk.

08:27.039 --> 08:29.473
Come on, Homer.
Japan will be fun.

08:29.575 --> 08:33.067
<i>- You liked Rashomon.
- That's not how I remember it.</i>

08:33.179 --> 08:35.203
Besides, if we wanna see
Japanese people...

08:35.313 --> 08:37.578
- we could have gone to the zoo.
- Homer!

08:37.683 --> 08:40.914
What? The guy who washes
the elephants is Japanese.

08:41.020 --> 08:44.353
His name is Takashi.
He's in my book club.

08:44.457 --> 08:47.688
Look, Mom. The safety instructions
are written in haiku.

08:47.793 --> 08:49.761
''Fasten seat belts tight.

08:49.862 --> 08:51.796
''Your seat cushions float gently.

08:51.898 --> 08:53.832
Headsets, five dollars.''

08:56.569 --> 08:58.469
[ Beeping ]

08:58.571 --> 09:01.665
Sir, it is not safe
to use electronic devices yet.

09:01.774 --> 09:03.674
- You're the waitress.
- [ Beeps ]

09:05.111 --> 09:07.705
<i>[ Attendant ]
Turn it back on.! Turn it back on.!</i>

09:07.813 --> 09:12.682
Ooh. I never knew Jim Belushi
made so many movies.

09:12.785 --> 09:16.312
Yeah, isn't it amazing?
They're filming one right now in the bathroom.

09:16.422 --> 09:18.822
Gonna be on towards the end of the flight.

09:20.459 --> 09:23.257
Toga! Toga! Toga 2,000!

09:23.362 --> 09:24.920
Marge, they stole my idea.

09:31.704 --> 09:33.831
<i>The local time is... tomorrow.</i>

09:38.177 --> 09:40.668
[ Homer]
Here's our room.

09:40.780 --> 09:44.272
Homer, you're supposed
to slide those doors open.

09:44.383 --> 09:47.045
I don't have time for that.
[ Grunts ]

09:48.754 --> 09:52.520
[ Man's Voice ]
Welcome. I am honored to accept your waste.

09:52.625 --> 09:55.458
- [ Beeps ]
- ## [ Bells ]

09:56.996 --> 10:00.022
[ Gasps ]
They're years ahead of us.

10:01.133 --> 10:03.795
Mom! Lise! Check it out. Dad's on TV.

10:05.171 --> 10:08.766
<i>- Oh, yeah!
- [ Marge, Bart, Lisa Screaming ]</i>

10:11.510 --> 10:13.603
[ Gasps ]
It's breathtaking.

10:13.713 --> 10:16.079
<i>Look. There's the Imperial Gardens.</i>

10:16.182 --> 10:18.082
<i>The Meiji Shrine.</i>

10:18.184 --> 10:20.243
<i>The Hello Kitty factory.</i>

10:20.353 --> 10:22.913
<i>[ Cats Yowling ]</i>

10:23.022 --> 10:24.922
<i>[ Yowling Stops ]</i>

10:25.024 --> 10:26.924
Who's up for some exploring?

10:27.026 --> 10:29.221
- Hey, I'm still checking outJapanese TV.
- ## [ Synthesizers ]

10:29.328 --> 10:31.387
Isn't this that cartoon
that causes seizures?

10:31.497 --> 10:33.829
[ Beeping ]

10:33.933 --> 10:37.391
[ Grunting, Groaning ]

10:37.503 --> 10:39.630
Bart, what are you doing?
[ Grunting, Groaning ]

10:39.739 --> 10:41.798
Hey, what the-
[ Grunting, Groaning ]

10:43.209 --> 10:45.109
Hmm. All right.

10:45.211 --> 10:47.771
[ Grunting, Groaning ]

10:47.880 --> 10:49.905
<i>- Robots be right back.
- Whoo!</i>

10:50.016 --> 10:52.746
- All that seizing made me hungry.
- Me too.

10:52.852 --> 10:55.218
Let's go to an authentic
Japanese noodle house.

10:55.321 --> 10:57.846
The toilet recommended
a place called Americatown.

10:57.957 --> 11:02.417
Dad, we didn't come halfway
around the world to eat at Americatown.

11:02.528 --> 11:05.827
I'd like to see theJapanese take
on the club sandwich.

11:05.931 --> 11:08.627
I bet it's smaller
and more efficient.

11:08.734 --> 11:11.635
<i>[ Man ]
We now return to Battling Seizure Robots.</i>

11:11.737 --> 11:15.332
- [ Beeping ]
- [ All Moaning ]

11:20.846 --> 11:23.576
[ Mechanical Clicking ]

11:23.683 --> 11:26.481
I can't believe they stuck us
at ''Tax-a-chusetts.''

11:28.020 --> 11:30.511
- Hey, you know, I once knew a man
from Nantucket.
- And?

11:30.623 --> 11:34.491
Let's just say the stories about him
are greatly exaggerated.

11:34.593 --> 11:36.754
Howdy, gangstas.

11:36.862 --> 11:40.127
I am average American Joe
salary-man waiter.

11:40.232 --> 11:43.690
These prices suck.
1 0,000 yen for coleslaw?

11:43.803 --> 11:47.000
Don't you serve anything
that's even remotelyJapanese?

11:47.106 --> 11:49.438
Don't ask me. I don't know anything.

11:49.542 --> 11:52.136
I am product of American
education system.

11:52.244 --> 11:57.113
I also build poor-quality cars
and inferior-style electronics.

11:57.216 --> 12:00.515
[ Laughs ]
Oh, they got our number.

12:03.389 --> 12:06.051
One square watermelon, please.

12:06.158 --> 12:09.855
Oh, my goodness.
Homer, those are $1 50.

12:09.962 --> 12:11.862
It's worth every cent.

12:11.964 --> 12:15.491
I'm tired of fumbling
with round fruit. D'oh!

12:15.601 --> 12:18.570
Well, maybe we should
just head back to the hotel.

12:18.671 --> 12:21.139
But you promised me
we'd do something Japanese.

12:21.240 --> 12:23.140
Oh, of course you're right.

12:23.242 --> 12:25.642
You know, I read
about a Shinto teahouse...

12:25.745 --> 12:27.713
where they practice
the traditional- Run, Bart!

12:34.520 --> 12:36.681
- Hey. Isn't that Woody Allen?
- Hmm. Looks like he's doing a commercial.

12:36.789 --> 12:37.414
Oh! [ Clears Throat ]
Hello.

12:37.523 --> 12:40.356
[ Clears Throat ]
So many rice crackers claim to be low-cal...

12:40.459 --> 12:44.327
but only Fujikawa rice crackers
make your interiors go bananas.

12:44.430 --> 12:46.489
What did I do to deserve this?

12:46.599 --> 12:48.499
Oh, right.

12:54.540 --> 12:57.839
Mmm. Fifty-dollar pretzels.

12:57.943 --> 12:59.843
Hey, what's Baby Huey doin'?

12:59.945 --> 13:03.881
- Says here they throw salt before
they wrestle to purify the ring.
- Hmm.

13:04.984 --> 13:07.748
- Spare some salt, tubby?
- Tubby?

13:07.853 --> 13:10.151
[ Speaking Japanese ]

13:14.059 --> 13:17.051
- Yoink.
- Hey, that's mine! [ Yells ]

13:17.163 --> 13:19.529
- Hey.
- [ Grunts ]

13:19.632 --> 13:23.068
<i>- [ Crowd Groans ]
- Like we say in my county, ''Hasta la vista, baby.''</i>

13:23.169 --> 13:27.071
Congratulations.
I am the emperor.

13:27.173 --> 13:29.141
Yeah? And I'm ''clobber-saurus.''

13:30.843 --> 13:35.371
[ Gasping, Sighing ]

13:35.481 --> 13:38.678
All hail Emperor Clobbersaurus.

13:38.784 --> 13:41.309
[ Booing ]

13:48.027 --> 13:50.587
Your wife has paid your bail,
Mr. Simpson-san.

13:50.696 --> 13:54.257
Thank God. Couldn't take another
minute in this hellhole.

13:55.301 --> 13:57.292
[ Chomping ]

14:03.542 --> 14:06.033
Now can we do something Japanese?

14:06.145 --> 14:08.340
Oh, I'm sick of doing Japanese stuff.

14:08.447 --> 14:12.781
In jail we had to be in this dumb
Kabuki play about the 47 Ronin...

14:12.885 --> 14:16.150
and I wanted to be Yoshi,
but they made me Ori.

14:16.255 --> 14:18.155
Then we had to do two hours of origami...

14:18.257 --> 14:20.350
followed by flower arranging
and meditation.

14:20.459 --> 14:22.484
[ Speaking Japanese ]

14:25.297 --> 14:27.265
Honey, I know you wanna seeJapan...

14:27.366 --> 14:29.664
but we're down to our last million yen.

14:29.768 --> 14:31.929
<i>Don't worry, ichiban.</i>

14:32.037 --> 14:34.403
I'll show you something Japanese.

14:36.876 --> 14:39.743
Oh, it's beautiful, Dad.

14:39.845 --> 14:44.248
It's a crane. TheJapanese believe
they bring good luck.

14:44.350 --> 14:48.013
Oh, be careful.
We need that money to get home.

14:48.120 --> 14:51.317
- [ Marge Gasps ] No!
- [Japanese ]

14:54.593 --> 14:56.493
<i>[ Man ]
Now, Mr. Simpson...</i>

14:56.595 --> 14:58.620
<i>I know you lost all your money,
but don't worry.</i>

14:58.731 --> 15:01.598
The United States
will not stand idly by...

15:01.700 --> 15:04.396
while one of its citizens
is stuck here like this.

15:04.503 --> 15:07.233
[ Grunts, Groans ]

15:07.339 --> 15:10.706
But, Mr. Ambassador,
how are we going to get home?

15:10.809 --> 15:13.903
Beats me. Try getting a job
and earning some money.

15:14.013 --> 15:16.880
That's what I did.
By the way, ''ambassador'' is taken.

15:19.018 --> 15:21.316
[ Groaning ]

15:25.190 --> 15:27.158
Every truckload of fish we gut...

15:27.259 --> 15:29.955
brings us 31 cents closer
to those tickets home.

15:30.062 --> 15:33.088
And I think I finally found
what I was put on this Earth to do.

15:33.198 --> 15:36.929
Knife goes in, guts come out.
Knife goes in, guts come out.

15:37.036 --> 15:39.436
Spare my life and I will
grant you three wi-

15:39.538 --> 15:41.733
- [ Screams ]
- Knife goes in, guts come out.

15:41.840 --> 15:45.139
Yippee! Time for the company loyalty song.

15:45.244 --> 15:47.906
## [ Singing ]

15:51.483 --> 15:54.008
[ Groans ]

15:54.119 --> 15:56.110
Well, this sucks.
What else is on?

15:58.590 --> 16:00.490
<i>- [ Bell Ringing ]
- [ Cheering ]</i>

16:00.592 --> 16:02.321
[ Laughs ]
Thank you.

16:02.428 --> 16:05.295
You have fulfilled our dreams,
and dreams of our ancestors.

16:05.397 --> 16:07.558
<i>[ Male Announcer ] Tune in tomorrow,
when another lucky family...</i>

16:07.666 --> 16:09.566
<i>tries to win their dreams...</i>

16:09.668 --> 16:12.865
<i>on Happy Smile Super
Challenge Family Wish Show.</i>

16:12.972 --> 16:15.702
<i>Family Wish Show. Hmm.</i>

16:15.808 --> 16:18.242
That gives me an idea.

16:18.344 --> 16:20.744
I think we all had that idea.

16:20.846 --> 16:23.906
I didn't. What is it? Lunch?

16:28.988 --> 16:31.047
Thank you, thank you.

16:31.156 --> 16:35.718
And welcome to our contestants
from America, the Simpson family.

16:35.828 --> 16:38.888
- You honor us.
- Don't patronize me.

16:38.998 --> 16:42.934
Now, Simpson family,
have you picked a wish?

16:43.035 --> 16:45.629
Well, I haven't talked it over with the family-
[ Chuckles ]

16:45.738 --> 16:49.230
but I think we'd all like
a free dinner at Americatown.

16:49.341 --> 16:53.402
No, no, no. We want
plane tickets home to Springfield.

16:53.512 --> 16:55.605
[ Cheering, Whistling ]

16:55.714 --> 16:59.582
Now, our game shows
are a little different from yours.

16:59.685 --> 17:02.017
Your shows reward knowledge.

17:02.121 --> 17:04.214
We punish ignorance.

17:04.323 --> 17:06.848
Ignor-What?
[ Screams ]

17:06.959 --> 17:09.051
- [ Laughing ]
- Okay, let's begin.

17:09.161 --> 17:11.060
Our categories are:

17:11.163 --> 17:14.530
<i>''Ow. That hurts. ''
''Why are you doing this to me?''</i>

17:14.633 --> 17:17.124
<i>- And ''Please let me die. ''
- [ Bell Dings ]</i>

17:17.236 --> 17:19.136
- ''Ow. That hurts.''
- Oh, yeah, number one. Definitely.

17:19.238 --> 17:21.229
I don't know.
I like ''Why are you doing this?''

17:21.339 --> 17:24.502
- ''Ow. That hurts.''
- We'll go with ''Ow. That hurts,'' Skip.

17:24.609 --> 17:28.204
- My name is Wink.
- [ Groans ]

17:28.313 --> 17:30.406
[ Laughing, Chattering ]

17:32.384 --> 17:35.114
All right, Simpsons,
whack the pinata.

17:35.220 --> 17:37.154
- [ Groaning ]
- Come on!

17:37.256 --> 17:39.451
<i>Whack that pig open.
Once more.</i>

17:39.558 --> 17:41.549
Harder. Whack it open.

17:41.660 --> 17:44.060
- [ Laughing ]
- Good. All right.

17:44.163 --> 17:46.597
You may remove your blindfolds.

17:46.698 --> 17:49.166
- [ Groaning ]
- Oh, sorry, Dad.

17:49.268 --> 17:51.668
- We didn't know.
- I had an inkling.

17:51.770 --> 17:54.864
- Could someone please whack my hernia back in?
- Sure, thing, Dad.

17:54.973 --> 17:56.941
Mr. Simpson, we'll cut you down...

17:57.042 --> 18:01.376
as soon as you answer
one question aboutJapan.

18:01.480 --> 18:05.143
- Is the answer ''Japan''?
- Actually, it is.

18:05.250 --> 18:07.411
[ Speaking Japanese ]

18:07.519 --> 18:10.886
That means you move on
to the lightning round.

18:10.989 --> 18:14.322
<i>- [ Moans ]
- [ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>

18:15.427 --> 18:17.361
- [ Screams ]
- He seems okay...

18:17.463 --> 18:20.398
but he is being burned internally.

18:23.502 --> 18:25.527
[ Screaming ]

18:25.637 --> 18:28.538
Hey, isn't that Homer
on theJapanese Channel?

18:28.640 --> 18:32.201
If that's Homer, then who the hell's
been puttin' beers on his tab?

18:33.479 --> 18:35.709
D'oh. Whoo-hoo.

18:35.814 --> 18:38.612
Uh-That boy ain't right.

18:39.785 --> 18:42.015
<i>[ Host ]
Congratulations, Simpsons.</i>

18:42.121 --> 18:44.146
The airline tickets are yours.

18:44.256 --> 18:46.816
All you have to do
is to pick them up...

18:47.993 --> 18:49.722
<i>from inside that volcano.</i>

18:49.828 --> 18:50.562
- Why are you so cruel?
- [ Laughing ]

18:57.436 --> 18:59.370
This vacation really blows.

18:59.471 --> 19:01.462
Well, at least we're past
the lighting round.

19:01.573 --> 19:03.666
[ Screams ]
Hmm. I see.

19:03.775 --> 19:08.678
I sure hope they don't have an ice cream round.
[ Screams ]

19:11.783 --> 19:15.685
Mmm. I don't think that bridge
can support much weight.

19:17.456 --> 19:20.857
Well, Maggie weighs
a lot less than- Oh, I'll just go.

19:20.959 --> 19:22.893
[ Groaning ]

19:24.963 --> 19:28.490
[ Together] Plummet! Plummet!
Plummet! Plummet!

19:28.600 --> 19:31.592
<i>Plummet.! Plummet.! Plummet.!
Plummet.! Plummet.! Plummet.!</i>

19:31.703 --> 19:34.331
Yes! Got 'em.

19:34.439 --> 19:38.739
- [ Together] U.S.A.! U.S.A.! U.S.-
- [ Buzzes ]

19:38.844 --> 19:41.472
[ Screams ]

19:41.580 --> 19:43.309
[ Gasps ]
Lisa!

19:46.919 --> 19:48.887
- [ Screams ]
- [ Grunts ]

19:51.557 --> 19:54.492
<i>- Oh.!
- Marge! Your shoe!</i>

19:57.796 --> 20:01.323
The plane tickets!
[ Grunting ]

20:01.433 --> 20:04.664
Whoa! Whoa!

20:07.339 --> 20:09.864
Oh, I'm afraid this might be the end.

20:09.975 --> 20:12.341
Well, at least we'll die
doing what we love-

20:12.444 --> 20:14.742
inhaling molten rock.

20:14.846 --> 20:17.610
[ All Screaming ]

20:17.716 --> 20:19.616
[ Cheering ]

20:19.718 --> 20:23.449
[ Screams ]
It burns! It burns!

20:23.555 --> 20:27.252
Don't worry, that ''lava''
is just orangeade...

20:27.359 --> 20:31.261
made by our sponsor,
Osaka Orangeade Concern.

20:31.363 --> 20:35.322
- It burns! It burns!
- It's loaded with wasabi.

20:35.434 --> 20:39.131
Kudos, Simpsons.
You have won your freedom.

20:39.238 --> 20:41.638
<i>[ Audience Cheering ]</i>

20:44.243 --> 20:46.211
Before I go, I want to say something.

20:46.311 --> 20:48.211
Game shows aren't about cruelty.

20:48.313 --> 20:50.611
They're about greed
and wonderful prizes...

20:50.716 --> 20:52.741
like poorly built catamarans.

20:52.851 --> 20:56.287
But somewhere along the line,
you lost your way.

20:56.388 --> 20:58.754
- For shame.
- [ Groaning ]

21:00.392 --> 21:02.383
Coming up next, a Canadian couple...

21:02.494 --> 21:06.328
who say they are
deathly afraid of scorpions.

21:08.667 --> 21:10.897
- Oh, that stings, eh.
- [ Screams ]

21:11.003 --> 21:13.233
- Ooh, God! Ow! Ooh!
- [ Screaming ]

21:13.338 --> 21:15.363
Sting those Canucks.

21:15.474 --> 21:17.738
[ Laughs ]
I love this show.

21:17.843 --> 21:20.676
Take that, you stupid hosers.
[ Groans ]

21:20.779 --> 21:24.180
<i>Good-bye,Japan. I'll miss your
Kentucky Fried Chicken...</i>

21:24.283 --> 21:26.547
and your sparkling, whale-free seas.

21:26.652 --> 21:28.415
- Hey, what's goin' on?
- What's happening?

21:28.520 --> 21:30.420
[ Beeping ]

21:30.522 --> 21:32.456
<i>[ Man On P.A.]
Folks, we're experiencing...</i>

21:32.557 --> 21:35.185
<i>some moderate Godzilla-related turbulence
at this time, so I'm gonna go ahead...</i>

21:35.294 --> 21:38.161
<i>- and ask you to put your seat belts back on.
- [ Screeching ]</i>

21:38.263 --> 21:41.198
<i>When we get to 35,000 feet
he usually does let go...</i>

21:41.300 --> 21:43.325
<i>so from there on out,
all we have to do...</i>

21:43.435 --> 21:45.426
<i>- [ Yawning ]
- is worry about Mothra, and we do have reports...</i>

21:45.537 --> 21:48.472
<i>he's tied up with Gamera
and Rodan at the present time.</i>

21:48.573 --> 21:51.599
<i>- Thank you very much.
- [ Roaring, Screeching ]</i>

21:54.346 --> 21:56.974
<i>[ Godzilla Screeches ]</i>

22:39.758 --> 22:41.726
- [ Murmuring ]
- Shh!

22:44.663 --> 22:47.962
<i>[ Homer Screams ]
Undo.! Undo.! [ Groans ]</i>

